subSubSection.paragraph:
This new species looks similar to 

A. mucida

, but differs by: head with anterior margin angulated at about 90° (slightly acute angled in 

A. mucida

); vertex 1.1 times as wide as long (1.1 times as long as wide in 

A. mucida

); frons with one obviously short median carina (median carina almost absent in 

A. mucida

).

